Bitstream ID:   2.
Description:    Sequence containing B-picture coded with maximum 
                vbv_buffer_size (1.75 Mbit) 
Stresses:       VLD
Justification:  A large B-picture located after several smaller coded 
                pictures can catch a decoder off guard.
Parameters:     Main Level, 31 frames
Organizations:  TCE-Hannover

Distribution of bits:   observe rule of maximum 2 macroblocks per row
                        that exceed legal 1.5:1 expansion factor.
 



Sqeuence                downconverted from HDTV "SKI"
resolution of picture   720 x 576
Syntax                  DIS
GOP structure           I-B-B-P....
picture structure       frame pictures
prediction mode         frame / field

bitrate                 15 Mbits/s               

Feature:		one B-frame with maximum # of bits
			only interpolated predictions
			(frame 10 in display order,
			 first B-frame of second GOP)

bitstream file          conf2.bits     
decoded image file      conf2.decoded  

format of decoded pictures:	raw format used in bitstream exchange AHG


